            "role": "assistant",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Foundry Agent Service is Microsoft’s managed runtime in **Microsoft Foundry** for building, running, and operating **AI agents** in production—not just chatbots. It ties together models, tools, orchestration, safety, and enterprise controls so agents can reliably execute real workflows (summarize documents, process invoices, handle support tickets, etc.) with visibility and governance. 【5:0†source】\n\n## What it does (core capabilities)\n- **Agent runtime & orchestration**: Manages agent conversations/threads, coordinates multi-step reasoning, and orchestrates **tool calls** (when the model decides it needs external data or actions).【5:0†source】\n- **Tool integration**: Lets you equip agents with “knowledge tools” (to retrieve grounded context) and “action tools” (to execute tasks) such as:\n  - Knowledge: Azure AI Search, file search, Microsoft Fabric, web grounding, etc.\n  - Action: Azure Logic Apps, OpenAPI-based actions, MCP endpoints, function calling, Azure Functions, browser automation, and more.【5:1†source】\n- **Trust, safety, and governance**: Enforces content safety and is designed to help with policy enforcement and production accountability/observability as part of the platform’s “trusted by design” approach.【5:0†source】\n- **Enterprise integration**: Designed to integrate with identity, networking, and observability systems so you can run agents securely at scale.【5:0†source】\n\n## How “tools” work inside the service\nYou attach tools to an agent (or per thread/run). When a user asks something, the model:\n1) interprets intent (and may rewrite the query),\n2) decides whether to call a tool,\n3) uses returned results to craft the final answer. 【5:1†source】\n\n## Web grounding options (classic docs, but useful conceptually)\n- **Grounding with Bing Search**: Agents can pull in near-real-time public web info and return answers with citations (you don’t get raw web chunks directly).【5:2†source】\n- **Grounding with Bing Custom Search**: Similar, but restricts retrieval to a **curated set of domains** you configure—useful for compliance and relevance. 【5:3†source】\n\n## When you’d use it\nUse Foundry Agent Service when you need an agent that:\n- goes beyond Q&A into **multi-step workflows**\n- can **retrieve** from your data and/or the web\n- can **take actions** (call APIs, trigger automations)\n- needs production features like safety controls and operational management.【5:0†source】【5:1†source】\n\nIf you tell me your scenario (internal knowledge assistant, customer support, invoice processing, DevOps helper, etc.), I can map the right tool set and architecture pattern for it.",
